182l1.364-6h5.366zm-8.73 6h-5l1.364-6h5l-1.364 6z"></path></svg><span class="small">Topics</span></a></li></ul></div></nav></div><script id="__NEXT_DATA__" type="application/json">{"props":{"user":false,"__N_SSP":true,"pageProps":{"category":{"id":4,"count":545,"description":"","link":"https://cms.bibleportal.com/category/what-the-bible-says/","name":"What The Bible Says","slug":"what-the-bible-says","taxonomy":"category","parent":0,"meta":[],"image":false,"_links":{"self":[{"href":"https://cms.bibleportal.com/wp-json/wp/v2/categories/4"}],"collection":[{"href":"https://cms.bibleportal.com/wp-json/wp/v2/categories"}],"about":[{"href":"https://cms.bibleportal.com/wp-json/wp/v2/taxonomies/category"}],"wp:post_type":[{"href":"https://cms.bibleportal.com/wp-json/wp/v2/posts?categories=4"},{"href":"https://cms.bibleportal.com/wp-json/wp/v2/bible-story?categories=4"},{"href":"https://cms.bibleportal.com/wp-json/wp/v2/bible_study?categories=4"},{"href":"https://cms.bibleportal.com/wp-json/wp/v2/quote?categories=4"}],"curies":[{"name":"wp","href":"https://api.w.org/{rel}","templated":true}]}},"posts":[{"id":34335,"date":"2024-04-25T03:06:09","date_gmt":"2024-04-25T03:06:09","guid":{"rendered":"https://cms.bibleportal.com/?p=34335"},"modified":"2024-04-25T03:06:11","modified_gmt":"2024-04-25T03:06:11","slug":"fasting-scriptures-for-perseverance-daniel-fast-journey","status":"publish","type":"post","link":"https://cms.bibleportal.com/fasting-scriptures-for-perseverance-daniel-fast-journey/","title":{"rendered":"Fasting Scriptures for Perseverance — Daniel Fast Journey"},"content":{"rendered":"\n\u003cfigure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"\u003e\u003ca href=\"https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/63794008d7aa43295425f847/87b3b0c3-ea79-45f5-af72-9d880ccaf487/Scriptures+for+Perseverance+Blog.jpg?format=2500w\"\u003e\u003cimg loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"1024\" height=\"683\" src=\"https://cms.bibleportal.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/ScripturesforPerseveranceBlog-1024x683.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-34336\" srcset=\"https://cms.bibleportal.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/ScripturesforPerseveranceBlog-1024x683.jpg 1024w, https://cms.bibleportal.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/ScripturesforPerseveranceBlog-470x313.jpg 470w, https://cms.bibleportal.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/ScripturesforPerseveranceBlog-768x512.jpg 768w, https://cms.bibleportal.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/ScripturesforPerseveranceBlog.jpg 1050w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px\" /\u003e\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/figure\u003e\n\n\n\n\u003cp\u003eWe all hit tough spots, those times when challenges pile up faster than our ability to handle them. And when we\u0026#8217;re in these moments, perseverance is key!\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\n\n\u003cp\u003eMaybe it’s a job that stretches your patience thin, a personal loss that feels like an aching, irreplaceable hole in your heart, or perhaps a goal that seems frustratingly out of reach. These moments test our perseverance.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\n\n\u003cp\u003eBut what exactly does perseverance mean in everyday life, and how can we keep pushing forward when all we want to do is flop in bed and pull the covers over our heads?\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\n\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eThe best encouragement comes from the Bible, the living Word of God, which still resonates powerfully today.\u003c/strong\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\n\n\u003cp\u003eScriptures show us the crucial role that faith plays in developing perseverance, emphasizing how\u0026nbsp;\u003ca href=\"https://www.danielfastjourney.com/blog/category/Faith+Life\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\"\u003eapplying faith\u003c/a\u003e\u0026nbsp;to our hardships leads to spiritual growth and maturity.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\n\n\u003cfigure class=\"wp-block-image\"\u003e\u003cimg decoding=\"async\" src=\"https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/63794008d7aa43295425f847/87b3b0c3-ea79-45f5-af72-9d880ccaf487/Scriptures+for+Perseverance+Blog.jpg\" alt=\"Scriptures for perseverance\" /\u003e\u003c/figure\u003e\n\n\n\n\u003ch2 class=\"wp-block-heading\"\u003eWhat Does \u0026#8220;Perseverance\u0026#8221; Really Mean?\u003c/h2\u003e\n\n\n\n\u003cp\u003eAt its core definition,\u0026nbsp;\u003cstrong\u003e\u003cem\u003eperseverance\u003c/em\u003e\u003c/strong\u003e\u0026nbsp;is steadfast endurance in the face of difficulty or delay in achieving success. It’s not just about the act of waiting; it’s how we wait.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\n\n\u003cp\u003ePerseverance involves mindset and attitude. It’s an active display of fortitude that keeps us steady on our path despite unexpected hurdles or the slow pace of progress.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\n\n\u003cp\u003eThis perseverance is an unwavering determination, a quality that remains steadfast and helps us stand firm.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\n\n\u003ch2 class=\"wp-block-heading\"\u003eWhy Do We Need Perseverance?\u003c/h2\u003e\n\n\n\n\u003cp\u003eLife is not a linear journey. We have times of steep climbing or unexpected curves and must overcome hurdles that test our spirit and will.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\n\n\u003cp\u003eThe world encourages us to move at a fast pace and buy the tools, pills, or programs that promise instant results. Whether it\u0026#8217;s 10 hacks for landing your dream job next week or a plan to lose 30 pounds in ten days, these unrealistic promises can mess with our expectations and distort our timelines.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\n\n\u003cp\u003eTruthfully, we can\u0026#8217;t always control the circumstances or outcomes of life. We all face trials, but God\u0026#8217;s Word says that suffering produces endurance, and endurance produces character. Instead of trying to fast-track or escape our problems, we can take a different approach:\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\n\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003e\u003cem\u003eEmbrace the process of building perseverance.\u003c/em\u003e\u003c/strong\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\n\n\u003cp\u003ePerseverance gives us the grit necessary to fight and win our battles, with the Lord as our anchor and source of hope! It keeps us moving forward through all adversities. Suffering and challenges are not just obstacles but opportunities for developing endurance, as highlighted in the Bible verses about perseverance you\u0026#8217;ll find below.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\n\n\u003ch2 class=\"wp-block-heading\"\u003eWhat Does Perseverance Look Like?\u003c/h2\u003e\n\n\n\n\u003cp\u003ePerseverance doesn\u0026#8217;t always look pretty when you\u0026#8217;re in the midst of the process. We love the end story: the triumph of the single parent who juggled multiple jobs to give their child a better future or the relentless pursuit of an athlete training for Olympic gold.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\n\n\u003cp\u003eBe encouraged: the end of the story will be beautiful, and it will make sense, but in the middle, there might be tears, questions, and doubts. Perseverance means you keep going\u0026nbsp;\u003cem\u003eeven when\u003c/em\u003e\u0026nbsp;you don\u0026#8217;t feel like it and\u0026nbsp;\u003cem\u003eeven if\u003c/em\u003e\u0026nbsp;things don\u0026#8217;t look the way you expected.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\n\n\u003ch2 class=\"wp-block-heading\"\u003eDrawing Strength from Christ Jesus\u003c/h2\u003e\n\n\n\n\u003cp\u003eWe have such a great cloud of witnesses, as the author of Hebrews tells us, and we can draw encouragement from their stories. These scriptural figures and their stories remind us that God is sovereign and watching over us, and we can persevere through our own trials.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\n\n\u003cp\u003eThe Bible tells many stories of suffering, challenges, and difficulties. We see figures like Job, who, despite profound losses, remained steadfast in his faith and integrity.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\n\n\u003cp\u003eAfter all, the Lord Jesus Christ Himself had to persevere through betrayal, opposition, and intense physical suffering, and it ultimately meant His triumph and fulfillment of His mission on earth.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\n\n\u003cp\u003eGod\u0026#8217;s love, as demonstrated through Jesus Christ, infuses us with the strength to persevere. Although we encounter trials in this world, Jesus has overcome the world and given us the promise of eternal life!\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\n\n\u003ch2 class=\"wp-block-heading\"\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eBible Verses About Perseverance\u003c/strong\u003e\u003c/h2\u003e\n\n\n\n\u003cp\u003ePerseverance in the Christian journey is not solely about enduring trials and tribulations; it\u0026#8217;s also about cultivating virtues that enrich our\u0026nbsp;\u003ca href=\"https://www.danielfastjourney.com/fasting-and-prayer\"\u003espiritual walk\u003c/a\u003e\u0026nbsp;in every season—remembering to praise the Lord in all seasons and be continually reminded of God\u0026#8217;s love.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\n\n\u003cp\u003eOur pursuit of perseverance enhances our relationship with God by adding layers of goodness, knowledge, self-control, and godliness to our faith.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\n\n\u003cfigure class=\"wp-block-image\"\u003e\u003cimg decoding=\"async\" src=\"https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/63794008d7aa43295425f847/84021a64-873b-443d-b66b-6a1a0d5dfb6f/Firm+Foundational+Devotional+Facebook.png\" alt=\"\" /\u003e\u003c/figure\u003e\n\n\n\n\u003cp\u003eHere are some Bible verses from the NASB2020 version that speak about perseverance and endurance.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\n\n\u003ch3 class=\"wp-block-heading\"\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eOld Testament Bible Verses About Perseverance\u003c/strong\u003e\u003c/h3\u003e\n\n\n\n\u003ch4 class=\"wp-block-heading\"\u003e\u003ca href=\"https://bibleportal.com/verse-topic?v=Job+17%3A9\u0026amp;version=NIV\"\u003eJob 17:9\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/h4\u003e\n\n\n\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cem\u003e“Nevertheless, the righteous will hold to his way, And he who has clean hands will grow stronger and stronger.”\u003c/em\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\n\n\u003cp\u003eThis verse from Job highlights the importance of remaining steadfast in righteousness. It promises that those who remain morally upright, despite challenges, will gain strength over time, emphasizing the value of persistence in right living.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\n\n\u003cp\u003eJob\u0026#8217;s perseverance is legendary. Although he lost everything and encountered unspeakable tragedy, God restored everything to him in the end.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\n\n\u003ch4 class=\"wp-block-heading\"\u003e\u003ca href=\"https://bibleportal.com/verse-topic?v=Psalm+27%3A14\u0026amp;version=NIV\"\u003ePsalm 27:14\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/h4\u003e\n\n\n\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cem\u003e“Wait for the Lord; Be strong and let your heart take courage; Yes, wait for the Lord.”\u003c/em\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\n\n\u003cp\u003eWaiting can be uncomfortable, but is often a necessary part of our journey in developing perseverance. David encourages believers to find strength and courage through their faith in God. The emphasis on waiting reflects a deep-seated trust in God’s timing and plans.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\n\n\u003cfigure class=\"wp-block-image\"\u003e\u003cimg decoding=\"async\" src=\"https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/63794008d7aa43295425f847/a97f3962-6e1e-474a-a410-bec273f887be/Psalm+27-14.jpg\" alt=\"Psalm 27-14 Bible Verses for perseverance\" /\u003e\u003c/figure\u003e\n\n\n\n\u003ch4 class=\"wp-block-heading\"\u003e\u003ca href=\"https://bibleportal.com/verse-topic?v=Psalm+37%3A34\u0026amp;version=NIV\"\u003ePsalm 37:34\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/h4\u003e\n\n\n\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cem\u003e“Wait for the Lord and keep His way, and He will exalt you to inherit the land; when the wicked are cut off, you will see it.”\u003c/em\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\n\n\u003cp\u003eThis Psalm encourages believers to\u0026nbsp;\u003ca href=\"https://www.danielfastjourney.com/blog/hearing-from-god\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\"\u003etrust in the Lord’s timing\u003c/a\u003e\u0026nbsp;and maintain righteousness. It promises that those who do so will be rewarded and witness God’s justice.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\n\n\u003ch4 class=\"wp-block-heading\"\u003e\u003ca href=\"https://bibleportal.com/verse-topic?v=Proverbs+3%3A5-6\u0026amp;version=NIV\"\u003eProverbs 3:5-6\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/h4\u003e\n\n\n\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cem\u003e“Trust in the Lord with all your heart and do not lean on your own understanding. In all your ways acknowledge Him, and He will make your paths straight.”\u003c/em\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\n\n\u003cp\u003eThis proverb teaches reliance on God rather than our own insights and knowledge. It assures that God will guide us in every aspect of life. Although sometimes we\u0026#8217;re unsure about the future, He will provide us with direct paths forward.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\n\n\u003ch4 class=\"wp-block-heading\"\u003e\u003ca href=\"https://bibleportal.com/verse-topic?v=Isaiah+40%3A31\u0026amp;version=NIV\"\u003eIsaiah 40:31\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/h4\u003e\n\n\n\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cem\u003e“Yet those who wait for the Lord will gain new strength; they will mount up with wings like eagles, they will run and not get tired, they will walk and not become weary.”\u003c/em\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\n\n\u003cp\u003eIsaiah offers a beautiful metaphor for spiritual and physical renewal. We can become weary in our daily walk, especially during trying times. But as this verse tells us, we can maintain our hope in God and find ourselves strengthened in His presence, allowing us to soar effortlessly above the turbulence.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\n\n\u003ch4 class=\"wp-block-heading\"\u003e\u003ca href=\"https://bibleportal.com/verse-topic?v=Lamentations+3%3A25-26\u0026amp;version=NIV\"\u003eLamentations 3:25-26\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/h4\u003e\n\n\n\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cem\u003e“The Lord is good to those who wait for Him, to the person who seeks Him. It is good that he waits silently for the salvation of the Lord.”\u003c/em\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\n\n\u003cp\u003eHere, perseverance is connected with silence and patience, highlighting that\u0026nbsp;\u003ca href=\"https://www.danielfastjourney.com/blog/connect-with-god\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\"\u003ewaiting for God\u0026#8217;s intervention\u003c/a\u003e\u0026nbsp;requires faith and trust. In the end, we experience God\u0026#8217;s love and goodness.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\n\n\u003ch4 class=\"wp-block-heading\"\u003e\u003ca href=\"https://bibleportal.com/verse-topic?v=Micah+7%3A7\u0026amp;version=NIV\"\u003eMicah 7:7\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/h4\u003e\n\n\n\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cem\u003e“But as for me, I will watch expectantly for the Lord; I will wait for the God of my salvation. My God will hear me.”\u003c/em\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\n\n\u003cp\u003eMicah expresses a personal commitment to looking to God for salvation with confidence that God will respond to his pleas, embodying perseverance in faith and\u0026nbsp;\u003ca href=\"https://www.danielfastjourney.com/blog/praying-for-strength\"\u003eprayer\u003c/a\u003e.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\n\n\u003ch3 class=\"wp-block-heading\"\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eNew Testament Bible Verses About Perseverance\u003c/strong\u003e\u003c/h3\u003e\n\n\n\n\u003ch4 class=\"wp-block-heading\"\u003e\u003ca href=\"https://bibleportal.com/verse-topic?v=Romans+5%3A3-4\u0026amp;version=NIV\"\u003eRomans 5:3-4\u003c/a\u003e: Suffering Produces Perseverance\u003c/h4\u003e\n\n\n\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cem\u003e“And not only this, but we also celebrate in our tribulations, knowing that tribulation brings about perseverance; and perseverance, proven character; and proven character, hope.”\u003c/em\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\n\n\u003cp\u003ePaul teaches that challenges should be faced with a spirit of joy because suffering produces perseverance, which in turn forges a refined character, leading to hope. If we want to see this progression in our own lives, we must realize that the starting link is tribulation.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\n\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003e\u003ca href=\"https://bibleportal.com/verse-topic?v=Romans+15%3A13\u0026amp;version=NIV\"\u003eRomans 15:13\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/strong\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\n\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cem\u003e\u0026#8220;Now may the God of hope fill you with all joy and peace in believing, so that you will abound in hope by the power of the Holy Spirit.\u0026#8221;\u003c/em\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\n\n\u003cp\u003eWhat do we do in times of discouragement? Ask God to fill you with joy and hope! This verse highlights the power of the Holy Spirit to fill us when we are depleted or in need of a spiritual boost.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\n\n\u003cp\u003eAs other perseverance Bible verses remind us, endurance strengthens our character and godly character produces hope.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\n\n\u003ch4 class=\"wp-block-heading\"\u003e\u003ca href=\"https://bibleportal.com/verse-topic?v=1+Corinthians+15%3A58\u0026amp;version=NIV\"\u003e1 Corinthians 15:58\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/h4\u003e\n\n\n\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cem\u003e“Therefore, my beloved brethren, be steadfast, immovable, always abounding in the work of the Lord, knowing that your toil is not in vain in the Lord.”\u003c/em\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\n\n\u003cp\u003eThis verse is a powerful call to all the Lord\u0026#8217;s people to be diligent in Christian life and ministry, reminding believers that their hard work and perseverance in the Lord\u0026#8217;s service have eternal significance and will not go unrewarded.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\n\n\u003ch4 class=\"wp-block-heading\"\u003e\u003ca href=\"https://bibleportal.com/verse-topic?v=Galatians+6%3A9\u0026amp;version=NIV\"\u003eGalatians 6:9\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/h4\u003e\n\n\n\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cem\u003e“Let us not lose heart in doing good, for in due time we will reap if we do not grow weary.”\u003c/em\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\n\n\u003cp\u003eWhen we don\u0026#8217;t see results or change, it\u0026#8217;s easy to get discouraged. However, Paul encourages believers not to give up on doing good deeds, promising that their efforts will eventually bear fruit at the proper time if they don\u0026#8217;t allow fatigue or discouragement to derail them.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\n\n\u003ch4 class=\"wp-block-heading\"\u003e\u003ca href=\"https://bibleportal.com/verse-topic?v=Philippians+3%3A13-14\u0026amp;version=NIV\"\u003ePhilippians 3:13-14\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/h4\u003e\n\n\n\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cem\u003e“Brothers and sisters, I do not regard myself as having taken hold of it yet; but one thing I do: forgetting what lies behind and reaching forward to what lies ahead, I press on toward the goal for the prize of the upward call of God in Christ Jesus.”\u003c/em\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\n\n\u003cp\u003ePast failures can haunt us and even put us to shame. But Paul reminds us to let go of the past, emphasizing the need to focus on the future. Continue to focus on spiritual maturity and fulfilling God\u0026#8217;s call.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\n\n\u003cp\u003eInstead of looking back, keep your eyes forward and with perseverance finish the race marked out for you.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\n\n\u003ch4 class=\"wp-block-heading\"\u003e\u003ca href=\"https://bibleportal.com/verse-topic?v=2+Thessalonians+3%3A13\u0026amp;version=NIV\"\u003e2 Thessalonians 3:13\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/h4\u003e\n\n\n\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cem\u003e“But as for you, brethren, do not grow weary of doing good.”\u003c/em\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\n\n\u003cp\u003eSimilar to the message in Galatians, this admonition reminds us to pursue righteousness and continue performing acts of kindness, even when we don\u0026#8217;t see results or rewards. We are called to steadfast love and walking by faith, not by sight, knowing that our faith produces perseverance.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\n\n\u003ch4 class=\"wp-block-heading\"\u003e\u003ca href=\"https://bibleportal.com/verse-topic?v=2+Timothy+2%3A12\u0026amp;version=NIV\"\u003e2 Timothy 2:12\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/h4\u003e\n\n\n\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cem\u003e“If we endure, we will also reign with Him; If we deny Him, He also will deny us;”\u003c/em\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\n\n\u003cp\u003eThis verse starkly presents the stakes of perseverance versus denial, associating enduring faith with reigning alongside Christ and warning against the consequences of denying Him. It shifts our perspective beyond the current earthly realm to the eternal life we have with Christ Jesus.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\n\n\u003ch4 class=\"wp-block-heading\"\u003e\u003ca href=\"https://bibleportal.com/verse-topic?v=Hebrews+12%3A1\u0026amp;version=NIV\"\u003eHebrews 12:1\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/h4\u003e\n\n\n\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cem\u003e“Therefore, since we have so great a cloud of witnesses surrounding us, let us also lay aside every encumbrance and the sin which so easily entangles us, and let us run with endurance the race that is set before us.”\u003c/em\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\n\n\u003cp\u003eThis verse uses the metaphor of a race to describe the Christian life. We cannot easily run this race marked out for us when carrying heavy burdens or sins that hinder our progress.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\n\n\u003cp\u003eEven when everything around you looks bleak, be encouraged that we have such a great cloud of witnesses around us, encouraging all of us who belong to the heavenly kingdom.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\n\n\u003cfigure class=\"wp-block-image\"\u003e\u003cimg decoding=\"async\" src=\"https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/63794008d7aa43295425f847/0ec3c6d4-efdb-463a-860a-1c9ceccd1cf2/James+1-12.jpg\" alt=\"Scriptures to pray for perseverance\" /\u003e\u003c/figure\u003e\n\n\n\n\u003ch4 class=\"wp-block-heading\"\u003e\u003ca href=\"https://bibleportal.com/verse-topic?v=James+1%3A2-4\u0026amp;version=NIV\"\u003eJames 1:2-4\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/h4\u003e\n\n\n\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cem\u003e\u0026#8220;Consider it all joy, my brothers [and sisters,] when you encounter various trials, knowing that the testing of your faith produces endurance. And let endurance have [its] perfect result, so that you may be perfect and complete, lacking in nothing.\u0026#8221;\u003c/em\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\n\n\u003cp\u003eHow could we possibly respond with \u0026#8220;pure joy\u0026#8221; when life brings trouble our way? Again, it\u0026#8217;s part of our maturation process. Suffering produces endurance and endurance produces character. As James says, this endurance leads to a perfect result!\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\n\n\u003ch4 class=\"wp-block-heading\"\u003e\u003ca href=\"https://bibleportal.com/verse-topic?v=James+1%3A12\u0026amp;version=NIV\"\u003eJames 1:12\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/h4\u003e\n\n\n\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cem\u003e“Blessed is a man who perseveres under trial; for once he has been approved, he will receive the crown of life which the Lord has promised to those who love Him.”\u003c/em\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\n\n\u003cp\u003eThe \u0026#8220;crown of life\u0026#8221; awaits those who remain steadfast in their faith despite trials and hardships. When you face trials, you\u0026#8217;re not alone. Know that your faith produces steadfastness, and your patient endurance will yield an eternal reward.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\n\n\u003ch4 class=\"wp-block-heading\"\u003e\u003ca href=\"https://bibleportal.com/verse-topic?v=James+5%3A11\u0026amp;version=NIV\"\u003eJames 5:11\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/h4\u003e\n\n\n\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cem\u003e“We count those blessed who endured. You have heard of the endurance of Job and have seen the outcome of the Lord’s dealings, that the Lord is full of compassion and is merciful.”\u003c/em\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\n\n\u003cp\u003eThis verse takes us back to Job\u0026#8217;s perseverance, holding him up as an example of enduring faith that leads to witnessing God\u0026#8217;s compassion and mercy. James reminds us not only of the suffering but also of the Lord\u0026#8217;s character and the end result.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\n\n\u003ch4 class=\"wp-block-heading\"\u003e\u003ca href=\"https://bibleportal.com/verse-topic?v=1+Peter+1%3A6-7\u0026amp;version=NIV\"\u003e1 Peter 1:6-7\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/h4\u003e\n\n\n\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cem\u003e“In this you greatly rejoice, even though now for a little while, if necessary, you have been distressed by various trials, so that the proof of your faith, being more precious than gold which is perishable, even though tested by fire, may be found to result in praise and glory and honor at the revelation of Jesus Christ.”\u003c/em\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\n\n\u003cp\u003ePeter certainly had to face trials in his life. This verse discusses again the joy in difficulties because we are confident in the purpose outcome.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\n\n\u003cp\u003eHe says the trials that refine believers are similar to the process of refining gold. As we stand firm in difficulty and trust in faith goodness of God, we can endure hardships while praising in the process.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\n\n\u003ch2 class=\"wp-block-heading\"\u003eFasting Builds Perseverance\u003c/h2\u003e\n\n\n\n\u003cp\u003eAs you can imagine, the spiritual discipline of fasting strengthens our patient endurance. It doesn\u0026#8217;t always feel enjoyable at the moment, but it bears incredible fruit. Though it can feel like testing, perhaps even suffering, you can still count it as pure joy, knowing the refining process is necessary.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\n\n\u003cp\u003eRemember these Bible verses about perseverance when you\u0026#8217;re fasting. Spend time reading them, writing them down, speaking them out loud, and memorizing them.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\n\n\u003cp\u003eChristian fasting teaches us practically about self-control and delayed gratification. Spiritually, our faith produces perseverance. Commit to being led by the Holy Spirit, your comforter, guide and advocate, and you will persevere through all trials—let God\u0026#8217;s presence continually strengthen you!\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\n\n\u003cp\u003ePlease be sure to pin these Bible verses about perseverance on Pinterest and share them with a friend!\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\n\n\u003cp\u003eRepublished with permission from Blogs.crossmap.com, featuring inspiring Bible verses about Fasting Scriptures for Perseverance — Daniel Fast Journey.\u003c/p\u003e\n","