://cms.bibleportal.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/full_earth_disc-eumetsatesa-1-john-4.19.png 565w, https://cms.bibleportal.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/full_earth_disc-eumetsatesa-1-john-4.19-470x470.png 470w, https://cms.bibleportal.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/full_earth_disc-eumetsatesa-1-john-4.19-150x150.png 150w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 565px) 100vw, 565px\" /\u003e\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/figure\u003e\n\n\n\n\u003cp\u003eIn Ephesians the church is presented as the Body of Christ, the one new man, and the wife of Christ. At the end of the Bible New Jerusalem is declared to be “the bride, the wife of the Lamb” (21:9). Although New Jerusalem is the consummation of the Body and the new man, they are not mentioned explicitly.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\n\n\u003cp\u003e\u003ca href=\"https://newjerusalem12.files.wordpress.com/2024/01/full_earth_disc-eumetsatesa-1-john-4.19.png\"\u003e\u003c/a\u003eThis shows that at the end of the Bible the emphasis is love—Christ loves His people and all His people love Him. First John 4:19, “We love because He first loved us.” In \u003ca href=\"https://bibleportal.com/passage?search=1+John+4\u0026amp;version=NIV\"\u003e1 John 4\u003c/a\u003e we love God, we love one another, and we love all people, This is possible solely because we love with Him as our love.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\n\n\u003cp\u003eIn\u003ca href=\"https://bibleportal.com/verse-topic?v=Revelation+2%3A1-7\u0026amp;version=NIV\"\u003e Revelation 2:1-7\u003c/a\u003e the Lord commended the church in Ephesus for many things but said faulted them in that “you have left your first [best] love.” We need to continually love the Lord above all, no matter how much we do for Him.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\n\n\u003cp id=\"Eph6-24\"\u003eEphesians concludes “Grace be with all those who love our Lord Jesus Christ in incorruptibility” (6:24). While we await His appearing, let us love Him with His incorruptible love, and not leave this love like the Ephesian believers left. Then we will love Him as “the bride, the wife of the Lamb.”Come, Lord Jesus!\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\n\n\u003cp\u003eRepublished with permission from \u003ca href=\"https://blogs.crossmap.com/\"\u003eBlogs.crossmap.com\u003c/a\u003e, featuring inspiring Bible verses about New Jerusalem, the Wife of the Lamb.\u003c/p\u003e\n","protected":false},"excerpt":{"rendered":"\u003cp\u003eIn Ephesians the church is presented as the Body of Christ, the one new man, and the wife of Christ. At the end of the Bible New Jerusalem is declared to be “the bride, the wife of the Lamb” (21:9). Although New Jerusalem is the consummation of the Body and the new man, they are\u0026hellip; \u003ca class=\"more-link\" href=\"https://cms.bibleportal.com/new-jerusalem-the-wife-of-the-lamb/\"\u003eContinue reading \u003cspan class=\"screen-reader-text\"\u003eNew Jerusalem, the Wife of the Lamb\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n","protected":false},"author":24,"featured_media":34084,"comment_status":"open","ping_status":"open","sticky":false,"template":"","format":"standard","meta":{"footnotes":""},"categories":[4],"tags":[1193,801,69],"source":"https://blogs.crossmap.com/stories/new-jerusalem-the-wife-of-the-lamb-tjZyG0DcG8duGTg2qrmue","bible_verses":"","article_author":"","external_link":"","topic_post":"0","topic":"","video_duration":"","_links":{"self":[{"href":"https://cms.bibleportal.com/wp-json/wp/v2/posts/34083"}],"collection":[{"href":"https://cms.bibleportal.com/wp-json/wp/v2/posts"}],"about":[{"href":"https://cms.bibleportal.com/wp-json/wp/v2/types/post"}],"author":[{"embeddable":true,"href":"https://cms.bibleportal.com/wp-json/wp/v2/users/24"}],"replies":[{"embeddable":true,"href":"https://cms.bibleportal.com/wp-json/wp/v2/comments?post=34083"}],"version-history":[{"count":1,"href":"https://cms.bibleportal.com/wp-json/wp/v2/posts/34083/revisions"}],"predecessor-version":[{"id":34085,"href":"https://cms.bibleportal.com/wp-json/wp/v2/posts/34083/revisions/34085"}],"wp:featuredmedia":[{"embeddable":true,"href